the pore, which acts as a particle reservoir at average chemical potential µ. µ is implicitly determined by the constant average density of water in the bulk system, which in turn is prescribed by simulating at constant pressure. Hence we can use the grand potential (T , V , µ) = −pV as the free energy to describe the subsystem in the closed and open state [24]. The equilibrium constant K is determined by the free energy difference between the closed (vapour) and open (liquid) state,

