Figure 5. Equilibrium densities of water (top row), sodium ions (middle) and chloride ions (bottom) in hydrophobic model pores of radii R = 0.35 nm to 0.75 nm; the NaCl bulk concentration is 1.3 mol l−1. The narrow 0.35 nm pore mimics the closed gate of nAChR whereas the wide 0.65 nm pore approximates the open channel. Although wide enough to admit the ions physically, the narrow pore is effectively
